Re: How to read 小火
by NileCat » Fri 04.15.2011 5:30 am @chikaraAs blutorange showed above, the word “ateji” usually covers wider meanings. If you want to use more technically accurate term, it is 熟字訓(じゅくじくん). But we call it ateji because it is “意味に当てた漢字”.　(although it is not “音に当てた漢字”)
